reviewText: My wife & I  finished watching the Spiderwick Chronicles a while back and we decided to order this movie on Blu-ray but it was kinds expensive.  I found this combo pack and it was cheaper, "What a Country!".  The movies were excellent and well made & relaxing to watch knowing that four letter words would not be used to generate a higher rating.  Although this was intended as a children's movie, we found it most enjoyable for adults.
Love both movies great for older grandkids

I mainly bought this for Stardust.  Stardust was an overlooked movie when it came out.  Maybe bad marketing.  Who knows.  It was a great fantasy adventure film.  Reminded me a little of The Princess Bride, but more fantasy elements.  It is a good time and not a bad movie for the family.  Spiderwick is a pretty good movie as well, but I couldn't beat the price for both movies.  Good deal.
Love both movies.  Got this for around $10 during holiday season.

Got this for Spiderwick chronicles. Getting stardust upgraded to bluray from dvd was just a bonus. This at the time of purchase was the price of either movie on bluray. so you really do get 2 for the price of 1 here. Each movie is on its own disc.
I've seen both films already on TV and I'm building a movie collection in Blue-ray so I couldn't pass up this deal.
This was a great deal I couldn't pass up! Both these movies are considered classics in my family. A great buy!
It was nice to find both on Blu-ray at such an affordable price.  Good fun for the whole family.  Check it out.
loved it!
Spiderwick was great, the Stardust was good: the first two hours of it. I've gotta admit, Robert DeNiro was a strange character (no spoilers)
Great quality
A+
Good value for these two movies.  Like them, worth owning.
Delivered in good condition though one disc was loose in case. Both movies played good.

This was a great package, because I got Stardust and my dad git Spiderwick, and we were both happy! He enjoyed his movie.

And Stardust is just a delight to watch. It's one of my favorite movies. It's humorous, romantic and action-packed. It's fairly underrated imo, so when you get a chance, check it out! It's probably not for everyone but take a chance anyway :)
great
I love Stardust, haven't watched Spiderwick Chronicles yet. Stardust is one of my favorite movies and far underrated IMO. Package arrived in perfect condition and I am pleased.

I'm really glad I found this. I just finished reading The Spiderwick Chronicles with my 4-year-old son and he was really excited to see the movie too. And we already love Stardust. Good movies and lots of extra features.
Liked Stardust a lot but the other one was not so great. But overall very entertaining.
Perfect video quality. Great bargain. Loved both movies.
Mainly purchased this combo pack for the Stardust movie; which is one of Wife's favorites.  Both discs are up to par with quality.

Bought this for the movie Stardust, it's a really good movie, loved the story and it has magic, witches and sword fights in it. It'll entertain everyone in the family. The other movie, The Spiderwick Chronicles is pretty good also, it's more for the kids definitely.
Always thought Stardust was under appreciated.
Both are great movies
Love these two movies.

Stardust although dated slightly with its special effects, was a magical delight to watch. I'd recommend it to anyone who likes a good old fashioned original fairy tale story, but this one is pretty much completely original.
Great movie for preteens and up.  To scary for younger kids
Both very great movies. My 4 year old son loves them!
A+
love this movie
I like the spiderwick chronicles. I LOVE Stardust. It's an entertaining, adventurous, funny, uplifting, goofy, swashbuckling, creative masterpiece
ok movie, not for kids, some of de Niro's scenes were so typical hollywood it ruined the movie.
Stardust is absolutely amazing. The Spiderwick Chronicles is just a really good bonus.
Came as expected! Awesome movies! Awesome delivery!
Both movies are great!!! I highly recommend this to anyone who has preteen children. I'm a senior citizen and my wife and I throughly enjoyed both movies. Maybe we're just young at heart and mind.
Stardust is one of my all time favorite movies.  Spiderwick was okay.  Played as expected.
